Business Brief -- VeriFone Inc.:
   Net Rose 58% in 4th Period
   As Global Sales Jumped
VeriFone said that its international business more than
doubled to $10 million in the quarter. Sales in the financial
segment of the U.S. retail market grew 18% from the year-ago
quarter, contributing 62% of fourth-quarter revenue.
   For the year, VeriFone reported net of $18.7 million, or
82 cents a share, compared with $12.2 million, or 55 cents a
share, the year before. Revenue in 1991 was $187.9 million,
up from $155 million in 1990.